org.hkijena.jipipe.api.data

Interface JIPipeDataImportOperation

  • All Superinterfaces:
    JIPipeDataOperation
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CopyContainingFolderDataImportOperation, CopyPathDataOperation, ImagePlusDataImportIntoImageJOperation, ImagePlusDataImportIntoJIPipeOperation, ImportImageJPathDataOperation, ImportJIPipeProjectDataOperation, OMEImageDataImportIntoImageJOperation, OMEImageDataImportIntoJIPipeOperation, OMEImageDataImportViaBioFormatsOperation, OpenContainingFolderDataImportOperation, OpenInNativeApplicationDataImportOperation, OpenPathDataOperation, OpenPlotInJIPipeDataOperation, OpenResultsTableInImageJDataOperation, OpenResultsTableInJIPipeTabDataOperation, OpenTextInJIPipeDataOperation, ROIDataImportIntoImageOperation

    public interface JIPipeDataImportOperation
extends JIPipeDataOperation
    An operation that is executed on showing existing data located in memory/cache The operations must be registered and will appear if the developer does not override the default importer row UI.

      • canShow

        default boolean canShow(JIPipeDataSlot slot,
                        JIPipeExportedDataTable.Row row,
                        Path rowStorageFolder)
        Checks if the import is possible
        Parameters:
        slot - the slot that is associated to the data. please note that the slot does not contain any binary data. it allows you to access the algorithm and graph.
        row - the row in the output table
        rowStorageFolder - the folder the row is storing the data
        Returns:
        if the import is possible

      • show

        JIPipeData show(JIPipeDataSlot slot,
                JIPipeExportedDataTable.Row row,
                Path rowStorageFolder,
                String compartmentName,
                String algorithmName,
                String displayName,
                JIPipeWorkbench workbench)
        Imports the data and shows it
        Parameters:
        slot - the slot that is associated to the data. please note that the slot does not contain any binary data. it allows you to access the algorithm and graph.
        row - the row in the output table
        rowStorageFolder - the folder the row is storing the data
        compartmentName - the name of the compartment that generated the data
        algorithmName - the name of the algorithm that generated the data
        displayName - a unique identifier for the slot
        workbench - the workbench that issued the command
        Returns:
        the imported data. null if not successful.
